        "title": "fix(cli): harden Windows node pairing and approvals",
        "body": "## Summary\n- preserve stable Windows node/device identity across reconnects and same-key metadata refresh approvals, while still rotating unsafe/stale/revoked/mismatched device tokens\n- harden node pairing approval authz, pending/paired node presentation, and gateway node-event routing so Windows nodes are less likely to fall back to manual/TUI repair paths\n- route devices/nodes/gateway CLI RPC helpers through direct local gateway-client auth for explicit loopback shared token/password calls, without letting stale inactive env/config tokens suppress device-token fallback\n- make host-native Windows exec approval get/set payloads work through the dedicated `exec.approvals.node.*` gateway methods, including native payloads that omit `payloadJSON`\n- block raw `node.invoke system.execApprovals.*` and keep exec policy mutation on the audited dedicated method path\n\n## Draft Snapshot\nCurrent pushed draft head: `8ee11cb653c2b3cbbecbc2c3180d7bdbe3ea47f9`.\n\nThis is still draft because `pnpm check:changed` is blocked by a repo-wide oxlint rule regression unrelated to this branch. The branch itself is pushed for review.\n\n## Proof On Current Head\n- Focused regression set: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/direct-loopback-gateway-auth.test.ts src/gateway/call.test.ts src/gateway/server.node-invoke-approval-bypass.test.ts` passed 2 Vitest shards, 113 tests.\n- Wider focused smoke: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/call.test.ts src/cli/direct-loopback-gateway-auth.test.ts src/cli/gateway-rpc.runtime.test.ts src/cli/gateway-cli/call.test.ts src/cli/devices-cli.runtime.timeout.test.ts src/cli/program.nodes-basic.e2e.test.ts src/gateway/server.node-invoke-approval-bypass.test.ts` passed 4 Vitest shards, 155 tests.\n- Targeted lint: `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/cli/direct-loopback-gateway-auth.ts src/cli/direct-loopback-gateway-auth.test.ts` passed.\n- Autoreview: `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main` clean, no accepted/actionable findings.\n- Azure pond refresh: rebuilt and restarted the gateway bundle at `8ee11cb653c2b3cbbecbc2c3180d7bdbe3ea47f9`; `openclaw --version` reported `OpenClaw 2026.5.30 (8ee11cb)`, gateway was listening, and explicit-token `health` returned ok.\n- Full Azure Windows-node smoke at `8ee11cb653c2b3cbbecbc2c3180d7bdbe3ea47f9` passed with two connected Windows nodes, pending=0, pairing intact, expected exec approval allow/restore/deny behavior, and raw approval mutation blocked from `node.invoke`.\n\n## Windows Node Pond Proof\n- Signed prerelease asset used: `OpenClawCompanion-Setup-x64.exe`, release `v0.6.0-alpha.14`, digest `sha256:36405bd72e2c11bae0aa051b551b339982a66ffb59820d977ad9983dbf0b4d98`.\n- Current pond has signed Windows nodes paired through the Linux gateway: paired=3, pending=0, connected=2; the connected Windows nodes reported caps=7 and commands=20.\n- Feature smoke passed on a Windows node: `device.info`, `device.status`, `camera.list`, and `screen.snapshot` returned successfully.\n- Exec approval smoke passed: `exec.approvals.node.get` returned enabled=true/default=deny/rules=22; raw `node.invoke system.execApprovals.get` was rejected with the dedicated-method error; temporary `echo *` allow rule was set via `exec.approvals.node.set`, `system.run` returned exit=0/stdout=`openclaw-clean`, the policy was restored to 22 rules/default deny, and a non-allowlisted `cmd.exe /c ...` run was denied by default policy.\n\n## Known Validation Blocker\n- `GOMAXPROCS=2 CI=true OPENCLAW_TESTBOX=1 pnpm check:changed` fails in `lint core` after ~896s because `typescript/no-unsafe-type-assertion` fires across unrelated core shards (`src/acp`, `src/auto-reply`, `src/infra`, `src/tui`, `packages`, etc.). Typecheck lanes skipped only because this sparse checkout is missing `ui/config`, which is expected under the repo sparse-safe path. This branch does not change lint config, package manifests, lockfile, or lint scripts.\n\n## Still Draft\n- Need resolve or waive the repo-wide oxlint blocker before marking ready.\n",
